\chapter{Database}
\section{Database software}
In order to store the information about users and data created by them, database has to be created. For the purpose of early states of the web site, XAMPP open source Apache distribution was used to manage the database, which offers MariaDB, Perl and PHP allowing the user to create their local server even without internet use. The distribution is primarily intended for Windows and Linux-based systems, MacOS alternative is Cyberduck.\\
PhpMyAdmin is an administration web application used to provide MySQL database for the web. The site itself is created in PHP and provided multiple functions to edit database tables such as creating, deleting or editing tables, table rows or managing primary and foreign keys. 
